definition: to push/to cut/to refuse/to reject/to decline/to shirk (responsibility)/to put off/to delay/to push forward/to nominate/to elect/massage

sentences.english: It has also been boosted by new Asian stores and weak sterling.
sentences.chinese: 新開設的亞洲專賣店和疲軟的英鎊也助推了它的增長。

sentences.english: ABAC declare a boost to the development of minor enterprises.
sentences.chinese: ABAC發宣言助推中小企業發展。

sentences.english: The boosting technology is important to improve the penetration ability of the earth penetrating weapon(EPW).
sentences.chinese: 應用助推技術是提高鑽地彈侵徹能力的重要手段。

sentences.english: We'll have to give it a push-start, I'm afraid.
sentences.chinese: 我看我們得用助推的辦法起動這輛車了。

sentences.english: At last, the drop-off of the carrier rocket means the satellite has entered its self-guided phase.
sentences.chinese: 最後，助推火箭的脫落意味着衛星已經進入自控狀態。

sentences.english: It is found that institutional investors aggravate the instability of financial markets.
sentences.chinese: 機構投資者是股市暴漲暴跌的助推器。

sentences.english: The interior ballistics synchronism of solid boosting rockets is discussed and analyzed.
sentences.chinese: 探討和分析了固體火箭助推器內彈道的同步性問題。

sentences.english: With the iPad tablet, Apple jump-started a product category.
sentences.chinese: 在iPad的助推下，蘋果開創了一個新的產品類別。

sentences.english: China’s natural rise could be turbocharged by its vast pool of savings.
sentences.chinese: 中國的鉅額儲蓄將大力助推其崛起。

sentences.english: The booster has spent the last week at Complex 40 after being assembled inside a hangar at the pad's southern perimeter.
sentences.chinese: 上週這個助推器在發射臺南邊的機庫組裝時情況複雜。

sentences.english: We had a fleet of colossal Saturn booster rockets emerging from our factories.
sentences.chinese: 我們的工廠裏陳列着成隊巨大的土星助推火箭。

sentences.english: God functions as a kind of booster for the absoluteness of self.
sentences.chinese: 作爲一個助推器的一種絕對的自我上帝職能。

sentences.english: A rocket propelled grenade blew off his forearms and hands and caused his femur on his left leg to be fractured.
sentences.chinese: 火箭助推榴彈炸掉了他的前臂，並造成左腿股骨骨折。

sentences.english: Supply shortfalls in grains and other foodstuffs have contributed to higher commodity prices.
sentences.chinese: 穀物和其他食品的短缺已對商品價格上漲造成助推。

sentences.english: Man's innovative ability is a drive-force of social development.
sentences.chinese: 人的創新能力是社會發展的強大助推力。

definition: to push (for acceptance of a plan)/to push forward/to promote/to actuate/CL:個|个[ge4]
to bolster/to give a boost to (the economy etc)
to crane one's neck/to await eagerly/to lead/to show the way
to promote (an idea or cause)/to advance/boost
to impel/to carry forward/to push on/to advance/to drive forward
